('99d6bb5d-f097-430d-9143-bb08b42025bb','Vs 5','L 1021',59.5629,16.3514,'[kra-hni- × lit × resa × s… …] + uas × farin + til + ekla-s [× (t)u i × sbelbuþa × --s(a)þu × helb]i × kuþ [× se… … … sigi · iuk × -u…]','"<kra-hni-> let ræisa s[tæin] … vas farinn til "Ængla[nd]s. Do i "Spiallbuða … Hialpi "Guð se[lu hans] … "Siggi hiogg [r]u[naʀ].','<kra-hni-> lät resa stenen … (Han) var faren till England. Dog i Sjallbodes … Hjälpe Gud hans själ … Sigge högg runorna.','<kra-hni-> had the stone raised … travelled to England. Died in Spjallboði''s … May God help his soul … Siggi cut the runes.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('c944a2b6-2a8d-49b4-90e5-b0f048f8a384','Vs 19',NULL,59.72,16.4182,'khu[nal-](r) · [(l)it … stain · þinsa ef]tir · horm · stob sen · trek| |ku-…n · auk · uas · farin · (o)(s)-r · miþ · ikuari · hiolbi k[-þ · salu h…ns ·]','"Gunnal[d]r let [ræisa] stæin þennsa æftiʀ "Orm, stiup sinn, dræng go[ða]n, ok vas farinn aus[t]r með "Ingvari. Hialpi "G[u]ð salu h[a]ns.','Gunnald lät resa denna sten efter Orm, sin styvson, en god ung man, och han hade farit österut med Ingvar. Hjälpe Gud hans själ.','Gunnvaldr had this stone raised in memory of Ormr, his stepson, a good valiant man. And (he) travelled to the east with Ingvarr. May God help his soul.','1040-talet',NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('3cfebb73-899b-4dc6-9eaf-526bb89462de','Vs Fv1992;173',NULL,59.6094,16.5411,'fu(þ)orkhn(i)…','<fuþorkhni[as]>',NULL,'<fuþorkhnias>','Början av 1200-talet (stratigrafisk)',NULL,'Knivskaft','Trä','Västmanland','Sweden'),
