('db0d8d83-2b99-4ccd-bf86-0f467855bc83','Vs Fv1988;36',NULL,59.6587,16.6131,'taf : lit : risa : estn : þina : hitiʀ : kri(m)ut ⁓ uas : farin : sun : (u)iþfast-- : aust:arla ulfr : auk : uibiurn : -… kitilas : krþi : b-…(u) · (o) : s---','"Taf(?) lét reisa stein þenna eptir "Grímmund. Var farinn, sonr "Viðfast[ar], austarla. "Ulfr ok "Vébjǫrn … "Ketilas(?)/"Ketilhǫss(?) gerðu b[ryggj]u á …',NULL,'Taf(?) had this stone raised in memory of Grímmundr. The son of Viðfastr travelled to the east. Ulfr and Vébjǫrn … Ketilas(?)/Ketilhǫss(?) made the bridge at …',NULL,'Tydliga spår av ursprunglig färg.','Runsten','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('e4a969fb-e4e6-4cba-96cd-225f9115ad79','Vs 26',NULL,59.7728,16.6008,'fuþorkhnias(t)b-ʀm ??? fu-','<fuþorkhniastbmlʀ> … …',NULL,'<fuþorkhniastbmlʀ> …',NULL,'Gyllentalsserien i runor.','Handkvarn','Sandsten','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('b0048863-7f26-448d-aad0-c4fbb070f4f3','Vs 15','L 998|L 999|B 1084',59.5989,16.8878,'§A × higulfr × lit × kira × merki × þisa × at × knut × faþur san × uk × kuþlug·u × ksistur × hanis × bali × riti × istaen × bali ⁑ knutr × §B × sten : hafir × riton × þon × stonta × mo × bali (h)i- rauþi × yftir × bruþ[u]r × bali','§A "Hægulfʀ let gæra mærki þessa at "Knut, faður sinn, ok "Guðlaugu, systur hans. "Balli retti stæin. "Balli. "Knutr. §B Stæin hafiʀ rettan, þann standa ma, "Balli hi[nn] "Rauði æftiʀ broður. "Balli.','§A Hägulv lät göra detta minnesmärke efter Knut, sin fader, och efter Gudlög, hans syster. Balle reste stenen. Balle. Knut. §B Stenen har upprest, som stånda skall, Balle den röde efter brodern. Balle.','§A Hegulfr had these landmarks made in memory of Knútr, his father, and Guðlaug, his sister. Balli erected the stone. Balli. Knútr. §B The stone has been erected so that it will stand, by Balli the Red in memory of (his) brother. Balli.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('593dddec-3624-43df-86d3-83eb87923657','Vs 13','B 242|B 1081|L 997|L 996',59.6299,16.6463,'× fulkuiþr × raisti × staina × þasi × ala × at × sun ×× sin × hiþin × bruþur × anutaʀ × uraiþr hik × runaʀ','"Folkviðr ræisti stæina þasi alla at sun sinn "Heðin, broður "Anundaʀ. "Vræiðr hiogg runaʀ.','Folkvid reste alla dessa stenar efter sin son Heden, Anunds broder. Vred högg runorna.','Folkviðr raised all of these stones in memory of his son Heðinn, Ǫnundr''s brother. Vreiðr cut the runes.','1000–1050',NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('ba01b014-4efb-4ea2-9bed-4207fd8d3131','Vs 31',NULL,60.1725,16.5911,'· (h)ulker · let · kera · bru · eftr (f)rota · sen · (a)ukut · ok · u(i)nut · sun · sen ·','"Holmgeirr(?)/"Holmgerðr(?) lét gera brú eptir frænda sinn "Auðgaut(?) ok "Vénjót(?), son sinn.',NULL,'Holmgeirr(?)/Holmgerðr(?) had the bridge made in memory of his/her kinsman Auðgautr(?) and Vénjótr(?), his/her son.',NULL,NULL,'Jordfast stenblock','Granit','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('68d1d85b-6377-44fb-90b4-b11eb6071372','Vs 16','L 771',59.6777,16.7311,'× ernbarua × lit × resa × sten × yf… … hristi','"Ernbiǫrn(?) lét reisa stein ep[tir] … risti','<ernbarua> lät resa stenen efter … ristade.','<ernbarua> had the stone raised in memory of … carved.',NULL,'ernbarua tolkas Ær(i)nbiorn i egennamnsförteckningen, s. 96.','Runsten','Granit med gulaktigt ytskikt','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('98a8232c-c9e0-4a67-86b2-60434513b2a9','Vs 20','L 1003',59.7304,16.5581,'tiori : ok : iuon : litu : resa : sten : ytiʀ : uibiorn : faþur … litli : risti · runiʀ','"Diuʀi ok "Ioan letu ræisa stæin æftiʀ "Vibiorn, faður [sinn]. "Litli risti runiʀ.','Djure och Johan lät resa stenen efter Vibjörn, sin fader. Litle ristade runorna.','Djúri and Jóhan had the stone raised in memory of Vébjǫrn, their father. Litli carved the runes.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Granit med mörka och grönaktiga inslag','Västmanland','Sweden'),
('90ffdc59-03e2-400f-9d77-9343dc2ed99c','Vs 27','L 1011|B 1086|L 1012|L 1010',59.852,16.5336,'þurbiorn ok : ikifastr : lit · resa : ytiʀ ⁑ sihþorn × faþur : sin × hon × toþr × [i] faru × litli × risti × runiʀ ¶ · […--keʀ · baþ : bru kera : r](u)(m)[ʀi]','"Þorbjǫrn ok "Ingifastr létu reisa eptir "Sigþorn, fǫður sinn. Hann [varð] dauðr í fǫru. "Litli risti rúnar. "…geirr bað brú gera rýmri.','Torbjörn och Ingefast lät resa efter Sigtorn, sin fader. Han blev död på utfärd. Litle ristade runorna. …-ger bad göra bron bredare.','Þorbjǫrn and Ingifastr had (the stone) raised in memory of Sigþorn, their father. He died on a voyage. Litli carved the runes. …-geirr ordered a wider bridge to be made.','Mitten av 1000-talet','Fragmentet, tidigare Vs 28, saknas.','Runsten','Granit med gulaktigt ytskikt','Västmanland','Sweden'),
